      "body": "Does this env var work for podman as well? Regardless, I am wondering if it was easier to just pass `--platform` to `docker build` in `./ci/test/02_run_container.sh` (and possibly `docker run`, if needed)?\r\n\r\nSomething like:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nCI_IMAGE_PLATFORM=\"\"  # native platform (default)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlternatively, with the added benefit of possibly supporting macos (see https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/31344#issuecomment-2493612110 (expand \"docker setup\")):\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nCI_IMAGE_PLATFORM=\"--os linux\"  # native arch (default)\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then in the individual CI tasks:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nCI_IMAGE_PLATFORM=\"--platform=linux/s390x\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
